    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_001951_0001" n="0001"/>
<lb/><opener><space extent="5" unit ="words"/><space extent="1" unit="chars"/><hi rend="small gray" resp="#U">132</hi>
<lb/>
<lb/><space extent="1" unit="words"/><dateline><placeName><geogName type="cataracts">Cataracts</geogName></placeName> <date when="1863-07-20">20 July 1863</date></dateline>
<lb/>    
<lb/><salute>My Dear <persName><choice><abbr>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi></abbr><expan>Doctor</expan></choice> Meller</persName></salute></opener>
<lb/><p><space extent="3" unit="chars"/>It has occurred
<lb/>to me since you
<lb/>left that possibly
<lb/>you might like
<lb/>to go at once down
<lb/>to the <placeName><geogName type="harbor">Kongone</geogName></placeName>
<lb/>where the Rapid is 
<lb/>to touch in <date when="1863-08">August</date>
<lb/>and leave the larger
<lb/>part of your luggage
<lb/>to go with "Pioneer"</p>
<lb/><cb rend="vertical"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Tell Waller I wrote him after church</p><!-- "after" is smudged, however easy to read. Should I code as such? BL. -->

	<pb facs="liv_001951_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">at the end of the
<lb/>year - The difficulty
<lb/>of luggage presented
<lb/>my thinking of
<lb/>this before the
<lb/><term type="occupation">bishop</term> came up
<lb/>but though we
<lb/>can scarcely ask
<lb/>it - if he could <!-- possibly "would", but unlikely. BL. -->
<lb/>be prevailed on
<lb/>to stop one day
<lb/>more you could
<lb/>give directions to
<lb/>the <term type="occupation">Steward</term> about<!-- "t" in about is completely faded. Only imprint visible. Should it be coded? Other words above have some faded, but still completely visible. BL. -->

	<pb facs="liv_001951_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>the bulkier articles <add place="above" hand="#U" rend="gray">133</add>
<lb/>being packed &amp;
<lb/>possibly be favoured
<lb/>with a passage
<lb/>in his boat to
<lb/><placeName>Mazaro</placeName> - Thence
<lb/>I write for a
<lb/>canoe to go down
<lb/>to the bar<!--possibly "bay"? Unlikely though. BL.--> of <placeName><geogName type="harbor">Kongone</geogName></placeName>
<lb/>for our stores
<lb/>and I could give
<lb/>you some pieces
<lb/>of cloth to pay
<lb/>your way in
<lb/>the matter of food

    <pb facs="liv_001951_0004" n="0004"/>      
<lb/>the wish of the <choice><abbr>Gov<hi rend="sup underline">t</hi></abbr><expan>Government</expan></choice>
<lb/>that salaries should
<lb/>cease by <date when="1863-12-31">31<hi rend="sup">st</hi> <choice><abbr>Dec<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi></abbr><expan>December</expan></choice></date>
<lb/>makes me mention 
<lb/>this plan though
<lb/>it may not be
<lb/>quite agreeable - Think
<lb/>about it - <persName><term type="occupation">Captain</term>
<lb/>Gardner</persName> says the Rapid
<lb/>will call "<choice><sic>as</sic><corr>at</corr></choice> the end
<lb/>of <date when="1863-08">August</date>" &amp; I write
<lb/>to the <term type="occupation">captain</term> to go
<lb/>round &amp; take our
<lb/>late companions off
<lb/>from <placeName><settlement type="town"><choice><orig>Quillimane</orig><reg>Quelimane</reg></choice></settlement></placeName><!--not sure if "village" is best tag. Please adjust as necessary. BL. --> so
<lb/>you might make up to
<lb/>them yet <persName>David Livingstone</persName></p><!--no true closer. Not using closer tags as that forces name below preceding text, which doesn't fit with the letter. Also <signed> tags fail to work outside of closer. BL. -->

            </div>
